, and what professors do when they're not teaching, No Place to Learn is a must-read: an eye-opening introduction that raises serious questions about the state of higher education in Canada. Current students, prospective students, and their parents will not want to miss this book, while professors and administrators would be wise to take note of it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSchoolszCanada. 0aUniversities and collegeszCanada. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aTupper, Allan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485019340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774850193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774850193/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles